description:
## What

Implement the `values.schema.json` constraints called out across the plan:

1. **`miroir.replicas > 1` requires `taskStore.backend: redis`** (plan §6, §14.4)
2. **`hpa.enabled: true` requires `replicas >= 2 AND taskStore.backend: redis`** (plan §14.4)
3. **`search_ui.rate_limit.backend: local` rejected when `miroir.replicas > 1`** (plan §13.21 + §14.6)
4. **Admin login rate-limit `backend: local` rejected when `miroir.replicas > 1`** (plan §4 `admin_sessions` / §13.19)
5. **`search_ui.scoped_key_rotate_before_expiry_days >= scoped_key_max_age_days`** (plan §13.21 "Config validation")
6. Any other "Helm schema rejects..." callouts found across the plan

## Why

Plan §13.21 Config validation paragraph is explicit: "such a configuration would cause rotation to fire immediately (or before) key issuance, producing a continuous rotation loop." These schema checks catch class-of-error misconfigurations at `helm install` time rather than at 3 AM.

## Details

Use JSON Schema `if/then` and `not`:
```jsonc
{
  "$id": "https://github.com/jedarden/miroir/charts/miroir/values.schema.json",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "miroir": { ... },
    "taskStore": { ... },
    "search_ui": { ... }
  },
  "allOf": [
    { "if": {...replicas>1...}, "then": {...backend==redis...} },
    { "if": {...hpa.enabled...}, "then": {...replicas>=2 AND backend==redis...} },
    {
      "if": {...replicas>1...},
      "then": {...search_ui.rate_limit.backend !== "local"...}
    },
    {
      "properties": {
        "search_ui": {
          "properties": {
            "scoped_key_rotate_before_expiry_days": {"type": "integer", "minimum": 1},
            "scoped_key_max_age_days": {"type": "integer", "minimum": 2}
          },
          "allOf": [
            {
              "not": {
                "properties": {
                  "scoped_key_rotate_before_expiry_days": {...},
                  "scoped_key_max_age_days": {...}
                }
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

**Test cases** (in `charts/miroir/tests/`):
- Each constraint has a `bad-values.yaml` that must fail `helm lint --strict`
- A `good-values.yaml` that must pass

**Error messages**: use `errorMessage` extension where operator-readable matters (e.g., "SQLite task store cannot run with multiple replicas; set taskStore.backend=redis").

## Acceptance

- [ ] 5+ bad-values.yaml files all fail `helm lint --strict` with clear messages
- [ ] good-values.yaml combinations pass
- [ ] Phase 9 CI includes the schema rejection tests
